This paper deals with the design and operation of DRAM chips, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and system-level design and implementation (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of mechanisms to dynamically adjust DRAM latency, which could fall under the categories of embedded systems (cs.ET), software engineering (cs.SE), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
